<h1 class="projector-city-library-box">How to Connect a Mac to a Projector</h1>
[/fusion_text][separator style_type="single" top_margin="0" bottom_margin="30" sep_color="#cecece" icon="" width="" class="" id=""][fusion_text]<strong>1. </strong>Turn ON your <a href="http://meetingtomorrow.com/apple-mac-computer-rentals">Mac</a>

<strong>2. </strong>Plug in theÂ <a href="http://meetingtomorrow.com/projector-rentals">projector</a> to an electrical outlet and turn it ON

<strong>3. </strong>Connect the video cable (usually VGA or HDMI) from the projector to the Mac. In order to do this, you will most likely need a <a href="http://www.apple.com/shop/mac/mac-accessories/power-cables" target="_blank">Mac adapter cable</a>. (Note: There are at least five different Mac adapter cables, which will vary depending on your computer's video inputs.)

<strong>4. </strong>Once the Mac and projector are connected, click on the <strong>Apple Menu </strong>in the top left corner of your screen

<strong>5. </strong>Select <strong>System Preferences </strong>from the drop-down menu

<strong>6. </strong>Select the <strong>Displays </strong>icon

<strong>7. </strong>When the Displays window appears, click the <strong>Detect Displays </strong>button

<strong>At this point your Mac and projector should be synchronized. If not, try following the steps below:</strong>
<ul>
	<li>Click on the <strong>Apple Menu </strong>in the top left corner of your screen (Step 4)</li>
	<li>Select <strong>System Preferences </strong>from the drop-down menu (Step 5)</li>
	<li>Select the <strong>Displays </strong>icon (Step 6)</li>
	<li>When the Displays window appears, select the <strong>Arrangement </strong>tab within the menu bar</li>
	<li>Check the <strong>Mirror Displays </strong>box in the lower left-hand corner of the window (Note: After checking this box, please wait several seconds. Once the displays are mirrored, you should see the same image on both your projector and computer.)</li>
</ul>
That should do the trick![/fusion_text][separator style_type="single" top_margin="15" bottom_margin="30" sep_color="#cecece" icon="" width="" class="" id=""][fusion_text]<strong>Meeting Tomorrow</strong> provides organizationsÂ and businesses with such servicesÂ as: <a href="http://www.meetingtomorrow.com/laptop-computer-rentals">computer rental</a>Â solutions, <a href="http://www.meetingtomorrow.com/lcd-projector-rental">LCD projector rental</a> solutions, andÂ <a href="http://meetingtomorrow.com/ipad-rentals">iPad rental</a>Â solutions. We also offer <a href="http://www.meetingtomorrow.com/sound-system-rental">sound rental</a>Â solutions.Â Give us a call at 1-877-633-8866.[/fusion_text][separator style_type="none" top_margin="" bottom_margin="30" sep_color="" icon="" width="" class="" id=""][separator style_type="single" top_margin="0" bottom_margin="20" sep_color="#cecece" icon="" width="" class="" id=""][separator style_type="none" top_margin="" bottom_margin="10" sep_color="" icon="" width="" class="" id=""][fusion_text]<a href="http://www.meetingtomorrow.com/atlanta-projector-rentals">Atlanta projector rental</a>Â |Â <a href="http://www.meetingtomorrow.com/baltimore-projector-rentals">Baltimore projector rental</a>Â |Â <a href="http://www.meetingtomorrow.com/boston-projector-rentals">Boston projector rental</a>Â |Â <a href="http://www.meetingtomorrow.com/chicago-projector-rentals">Chicago projector rental</a>Â |Â <a href="http://www.meetingtomorrow.com/denver-projector-rentals">Denver projector rental</a>Â |Â <a href="http://www.meetingtomorrow.com/detroit-projector-rentals">Detroit projector rental</a>Â |Â <a href="http://www.meetingtomorrow.com/fort-lauderdale-projector-rentals">Fort Lauderdale projector rental</a>Â |Â <a href="http://www.meetingtomorrow.com/fort-worth-projector-rentals">Fort Worth projector rental</a>Â |Â <a href="http://www.meetingtomorrow.com/houston-projector-rentals">Houston projector rental</a>Â |Â <a href="http://www.meetingtomorrow.c